1 (e) (4) (i) Except as provided in paragraph (5) of this subsection, from the
2 fines collected by a political subdivision as a result of violations enforced by speed
3 monitoring systems, work zone speed control systems, stop sign monitoring systems, school
4 bus monitoring cameras, bus lane monitoring systems, or noise abatement monitoring
5 systems, a political subdivision:
6 1. May recover the costs of implementing and administering
7 the speed monitoring systems, work zone speed control systems, school bus monitoring
8 cameras, bus lane monitoring systems, or noise abatement monitoring systems; and
9 2. Subject to subparagraphs (ii), (iii), and (iv) of this
10 paragraph, may spend any remaining balance solely for public safety purposes, including
11 pedestrian or highway safety programs.
12 (VII) 1. THE GOVERNING BODY OF BALTIMORE COUNTY
13 SHALL ESTABLISH, BY LAW, A SPECIAL FUND THAT MAY BE USED ONLY TO ASSIST IN
14 COVERING THE COST OF SITING, CONSTRUCTING, INSTALLING, AND MAINTAINING
15 TRAFFIC CALMING DEVICES ON COUNTY ROADS.
16 2. FROM THE FINES COLLECTED BY BALTIMORE
17 COUNTY AS A RESULT OF VIOLATIONS ENFORCED BY SPEED MONITORING SYSTEMS,
18 ANY BALANCE REMAINING AFTER THE ALLOCATION OF FINES UNDER
19 SUBPARAGRAPH (I)1 OF THIS PARAGRAPH SHALL BE DEPOSITED INTO THE SPECIAL
20 FUND REQUIRED UNDER SUBSUBPARAGRAPH 1 OF THIS SUBPARAGRAPH.
21 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
22 October 1, 2025.

